+ When you create a Google form, you can specify a [destination][1] spreadsheet for the responses
+ You can access the response store in this spreadsheet with Apps Script and e.g. create an additional column where the responses to your questions are merged to `CourseCodeCourseNo-Class`.
+ You can evaluate the response to the question `Department` and synchronize the response row to a secondary spreadsheet - depending on the response value
+ You can implement an [installable On Form Submit trigger for spreadsheets][2] to automatically synchronize the secondary sheets on each form submit.


Below is an example code meeting your needs. Please refer to Apps Script documentation for [Google Forms][3] and [Google Spreadsheets][4] to obtain a better understanding and modify the sample as desired.

**Sample:**
```lang:js
function myFunction() {
  var ss=SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();
  var sheet=ss.getActiveSheet();
